        "id": "66779781-f383-403c-a961-b5e4e600f4e4",
        "text": "Infrequently-used serverless code may suffer from greater response latency ([[latency (engineering)]]) than code that is continuously running on a dedicated server, virtual machine, or container. This is because, unlike with autoscaling, the cloud provider typically \"spins down\" the serverless code completely when not in use. This means that if the runtime (for example, the Java ([[Java (programming language)]]) runtime) requires a significant amount of time to start up, it will create additional latency.  - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serverless_Computing#Disadvantages wikipedia]"
