      "id": "6a6aacd7-9ce8-452b-8065-664615d47046",
      "text": "- **Cost:**  Serverless is more cost-effective than renting or purchasing a fixed quantity of servers, which generally involves significant periods of underutilization or idle time. It can even be more cost-efficient than provisioning an autoscaling group ([[autoscaling]]), due to more efficient bin-packing ([[Bin packing problem]]) of the underlying machine resources - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serverless_Computing#Advantages wikipedia]"
    },
