      "text": "# Disadvantages\nThe disadvantages of serverless computing can be described under the following headings:\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "66779781-f383-403c-a961-b5e4e600f4e4",
      "text": "- **Latency:** Infrequently-used serverless code may suffer from greater response latency than code that is continuously running on a dedicated server, virtual machine, or container  - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serverless_Computing#Disadvantages wikipedia]"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "af3f6cbf-19e1-4158-9275-437ec1fae27f",
      "text": "- **Resource limits:** Serverless computing is not suited to some computing workloads, such as [[high-performance computing]], because of the resource limits imposed by cloud providers, and also because it would likely be cheaper to bulk-provision the number of servers believed to be required at any given point in time."
    },
